Valves round-elliptical, relatively small. The SV is coarsely striated and punctuated, usually with no axial rows of areolae. The SV sternum is large and composed of two lanceolate parts (
Figs 27–29, 33
), one median SV stria lacking on one side (
Fig. 27
, arrow) or both (
Fig. 33
). The RV has coarsely punctuated striae, strongly radiate. The RV fascia is narrow and wide (often more than half a valve in length). The raphe is often slightly sigmoid with helictoglossae deflected towards opposite sides (
Fig. 34
). Slide BM 19589 only shows the variety β.
